{"build_type":"library","description":"Push a 4xi64 task record [type,a,b,c] onto the per-thread explicit lowering worklist stack. g_wl_base/g_wl_top are thread-local (registered in the de-globalization TLS offset table), so under the packed concurrent compile-worker fan-out each worker owns its own worklist with no cross-thread contention. Buffer (2MiB / 65536 records) is lazily allocated once per worker from its own growable arena via allocate-character-buffer-inside-memory-arena and reused for every function that worker lowers. Bounds-checked and allocation-checked: fails hard via report_error_and_exit on overflow or allocation denial, never silently truncates. Replaces the recursive lower-instruction-array edge so native lowering runs at constant native-stack depth.","module_name":"enqueue-compilation-process-worklist-stack","package_name":"enqueue-compilation-process-worklist-stack","function_definitions":{"enqueue-compilation-process-worklist-stack":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"ttype","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"a","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"b","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"c","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"cap","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":262144},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"bufsize","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2097152},{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"base","name":"g